  <refnamediv>
    <refname>rboot</refname>
    <refpurpose>Simulate a bootstrap resample</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   z=rboot(x)
   z=rboot(x,b)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x :</term>
      <listitem><para> a nrows-by-ncols matrix of doubles</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>b :</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1-by-1 matrix of doubles, the number of bootstrap resamples (default b=1)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>z :</term>
      <listitem><para> a nrows-by-(ncols*b) matrix of doubles</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
<literal>rboot(x)</literal> gives a resample of x.
   </para>
   <para>
<literal>rboot(x,b)</literal> gives b columns of resamples. This form works
only for x one-dimensional, ie x column vector.
   </para>
   <para>
If x is a row vector, it is converted into
a column vector.
   </para>
   <para>
If x is a matrix, the resamples are stored in the columns of z:
<screen>
z=[z1,z2,...,zb]
</screen>
where zi is a nrows-by-ncols matrix of doubles, for i=1,2,...,b.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
// With x column vector
x=distfun_chi2rnd(3,10,1)
z=rboot(x)
// Get 3 resamples
z=rboot(x,3)

// With a x matrix
x=distfun_chi2rnd(3,10,3)
z=rboot(x)
// Get 3 resamples
z=rboot(x,3)

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

